   <abstract>This image most likely shows Hubert Renfro Knickerbocker (1898-1949), who was a prominent foreign correspondent for such newspapers as the New York Evening Post and the Philadelphia Public Ledger. He covered such conflicts as the Italo-Abyssinian War (1935-1936), the Spanish Civil War (1936-1937), and the Sino-Japanese War (1937) before working in Europe during World War II. He also taught journalism at Southern Methodist University (1922-1923) and wrote a number of books.</abstract>
